        "title": "fix(sessions): auto-generate session titles via AI summarization",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #77165 — auto-generate session titles via AI summarization after configurable user turns.\n\n- Problem: Session titles are derived from truncated first-user messages, which are uninformative\n- Solution: After configurable turns (default 3), call the model to summarize the conversation into a short title\n- What changed: Added session-title-generator, wired into get-reply-run, added UI display via derivedTitle\n- What did NOT change: No other components were affected. Manual session renaming still works as before.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Session titles were truncated first-user messages; now AI-generated after configurable turns.\n- **Real environment tested:** Linux x86_64, Node 22, local OpenClaw checkout with `pnpm gateway:dev`, DeepSeek model.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  ```bash\n  # Start gateway with sessionTitle config\n  cd /path/to/openclaw\n  pnpm gateway:dev\n\n  # Create new session, send 1 message, verify no autoTitle\n  # Send 2 more messages (total 3), verify autoTitle generated\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  ```\n  $ grep autoTitle /tmp/openclaw-test/.openclaw-dev/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json\n  autoTitle=Test conversation\n  autoTitle=1+1 equals 2\n  autoTitle=Hi, who are you?\n  ```\n  Control UI sidebar displays \"Test conversation\", \"1+1 equals 2\", \"Hi, who are you?\" instead of session keys.\n- **Observed result after fix:** AI-generated titles appear in session store and Control UI sidebar after 3 user turns (configurable via sessionTitle.turnsBeforeTitle). 1 turn does not trigger title generation. Heartbeat messages are correctly excluded from turn count.\n- **What was not tested:** Live multi-agent production workspace; tested with single-agent dev gateway only.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- Coverage level: Runtime integration test\n- Target test file: src/auto-reply/reply/session-title-generator.ts (existing test from original PR)\n- Scenario locked in: Session titles are generated after turnsBeforeTitle user turns and displayed in UI\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: The title generator is self-contained with clear early-return conditions\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- Root cause: No mechanism existed to generate descriptive session titles from conversation content\n- Missing detection / guardrail: Session title was only firstUserMessage truncation, no AI summarization",
